All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Board
The Board class is a JavaFX application that represents a board game with players and various types of hurdles.
Dice
The Dice class represents a dice with a value that can be rolled.
FenceHurdle
The FenceHurdle class represents a fence obstacle in a game.
FireHurdle
The FireHurdle class represents a fire obstacle in a game.
Hurdles
The Hurdles interface represents an obstacle that a player may encounter in a game.
JSimonRace
The JSimonRace class represents a game where players race to reach the end of a board by rolling dice and moving their pieces.
Move
The Move class represents a player's movement on a board in a game.
PitHurdle
The PitHurdle class represents a pit obstacle in a game.
Player
The Player class extends the Circle class from the JavaFX library and represents a player in a game.
Position
The Position class represents the x and y coordinates of a point in a two-dimensional plane.
ScoreCard
The ScoreCard class represents a player's score in the game.
TeleportationHurdle
TeleportationHurdle is a class that represents a teleportation hurdle in a game.
Tile
The Tile class represents a single tile on the board in the JSimonRace game.
